These two snippets are **code-behind** and must be pasted behind their objects in the Project Explorer, not into standard modules.

### `ThisWorkbook`

Keeps the working sheets hidden on open and lands on the Dashboard.

```vba
'=================================================================
' ThisWorkbook  (code-behind)
'
' HOW TO INSTALL:
'   In the VBA editor, double-click "ThisWorkbook" under
'   VBAProject (YourFile.xlsm) in the Project Explorer and paste the
'   code below into that code pane. Do NOT put this in a standard
'   module — it must live behind the ThisWorkbook object to receive
'   the Workbook_Open event.
'=================================================================
Option Explicit

Private Sub Workbook_Open()
    ' Keep the working sheets hidden from the user every time the file
    ' opens, and land them on the Dashboard.
    On Error Resume Next

    If SheetExists(SHEET_PLACEHLDR) Then
        ThisWorkbook.Worksheets(SHEET_PLACEHLDR).Visible = xlSheetVeryHidden
    End If
    If SheetExists(SHEET_ALT) Then
        ThisWorkbook.Worksheets(SHEET_ALT).Visible = xlSheetVeryHidden
    End If

    If SheetExists(SHEET_DASHBOARD) Then
        ThisWorkbook.Worksheets(SHEET_DASHBOARD).Activate
    End If

    On Error GoTo 0
End Sub
```

