## Adding a new transaction type later (the whole procedure)

1. Author a Word template with `<<Placeholder>>` tags and any `<<ALT_Section_Option_START>>…_END>>` blocks. Save it as `.docx`.
2. Put it in the `Templates` folder (or anywhere; use an absolute path).
3. Add one row to **Config**: type name, template path, a new `Transaction_*` sheet name, description.
4. On the Dashboard, pick the new type and click **Load Transaction**. The sheet, fields and dropdowns appear automatically.

No VBA changes. Ever.
